    • Method Detail

      • toDot

        public final java.lang.String toDot(java.io.FileWriter where)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Writes in the specified file a dot representation of the abstract syntax of this type. By default, it writes a single dot node for this node of abstract syntax and it calls the auxiliary toDotAux(FileWriter) method. Subclasses should redefine the latter in order to consider components of types.
        Parameters:
        where - the file where the dot representation must be written
        Returns:
        the name used to refer to this node in the dot file, as computed by Absyn.dotNodeName()
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if there is a problem while writing into the file

      • typeCheck

        public final Type typeCheck()
        Type-checks this type expression. It calls the auxiliary method typeCheckAux() and stores the resulting semantical type into staticType.
        Returns:
        the semantical type corresponding to this type expression

      • toType

        public final Type toType()
        Yields the semantical type corresponding to this type expression. It calls the auxiliary method toTypeAux() and stores the resulting semantical type into staticType. The difference with typeCheck() is that class types occurring in this type expressions are not type-checked themselves.
        Returns:
        the semantical type corresponding to this type expression

      • getStaticType

        public final Type getStaticType()
        Yields the static semantical type of this type expression, as computed during last type-checking.
        Returns:
        the static semantical type of this type expression, if it has already been type-checked. Yields null otherwise
